      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 1,
      "message": "Should we update the current model with a new revision like that ? \n\nAre we still ok with because we know that CPS does not have any use case with some data yet ? Because as soon as we start having data we can not do that anymore, as existing data instances compliant to any previous model will be incompatible with the new model. At some point we'll have to \"insert\" new revisions of existing model instead of updating. Is there any reason why not staring doing it now ?\n\nFor https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/cps/+/121124 we made an update because the model format was broken and and the model we had was unusable.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
