    {
      "id": "9004c961_c2f39da0",
      "file_path": "cps-ri/src/main/resources/changelog/db/changes/10-add-root-container-cps-ran-model-forward.sql",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 1,
      "message": "Yes, as long as there is no data attached to the module we are ok.\n\nThe good thing with starting simulating in the database what will be done later on with NCMP API is that it starts building our understanding and experience with the process and how it would work.\n\nAnother advantage would be that it is much more easy and less error prone do do inserts and deletes than updates.\n\nWe can ask ourselves these questions next time if ever we have to do it again.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2021-06-19 00:27:52.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "28ab464f_7dd5856b",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "953d949c_0b5392e9",
      "file_path": "cps-ri/src/main/resources/changelog/db/changes/10-add-root-container-cps-ran-model-rollback.sql",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 45,
      "message": "Exact, this is the principle of rollback.\n\nWhen any deployment is done, if for what ever reason something goes wrong and makes the system  worse than what it was with the previous version, the operations teams should have the option either to quick fix forward or rollback to the previous state, as if nothing has been ever touched.\n\nAnd here these little incremental liquibase rollbacks need to be thought in a more global rollback process of an operator running CPS Honolulu in Production, then going for a deployment of CPS Istanbul, having a serious issue and decide to go back to CPS Honolulu. From an application perspective this is easy to do, but much more delicate at the database level.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2021-06-19 00:27:52.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "d8a8d31e_7ba7cc61",
      "unresolved": true
    },
